cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with evaluating the performance of local feature detectors in images.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as feature detection is an important task in AI applications such as object recognition and tracking.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as machine learning techniques are often used in feature detection.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as feature detection can also be used in image retrieval systems.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely but possible sub-category as feature detection is an important task in multimedia applications such as video analysis and editing.
